Title: ⚠️உஷார் மக்களே.! *Redmi Note 14 Series* 🥴|⭐️Tech SuperStar⭐️
Description:
The video reviews Redmi Note 14 Series, that consists of Redmi Note 14, Redmi Note 14 Pro & Redmi Note 14 Pro+. Firstly, Redmi Note 14 has launched with 3 different colour varients with the price of ₹18,999, decent performance with Diamond City 7025 Ultra and supports gaming features. The mobile is embedded with good design & display specifications, has IP rating 64 that supports wet touch screen. It has a quiet good camera specifications but poor video quality.It has 5110mAh battery performance, hyper OS support & some Ai features. The second mobile shown here is Redmi Note 14 Pro, that has comfortable design & quality, has Diamond City 7300 Ultra. It has so much bloatwares & ads, has IP 66,68,69 rating priced ₹24,999. It has 5800mAh battery support and has decent photo, video quality & Ai features. The final mobile featured here is Redmi Note 14 Pro+, which has a solid quality & design. It has Snapdragon 7S Gen 3 processor & 6200mAh battery support. It has the same Camera features as in Redmi Note 14 Pro & it's not so good for gaming. This video also addresses some common doubts on Redmi's sales strategy and compares the today's situation of Redmi mobiles with the previously launched ones. To conclude, Redmi Note 14 Series definitely has some upgrades while comparing it with the previous launches, but which are not upto the mark. Title: Why are TV's so disposable? Hisense WiFi / storage full bootloop #tech #pc #technology #shorts
Description: This isn't a sympathy video, I'm just opening up to share my personal experience of how cost cutting and poor manufacturing in today's tech impacts vulnerable groups the most, especially the poor and disabled. From a PC to a laptop, releasing a subpar device and ignoring the QC issues is a common practice. Hisense isn't alone in this, it's a known secret that Smart TV's use the cheapest IC's available, and if you want your TV to last, you should never use the built-in apps. The fact this is acceptable on thousand dollar devices is disgusting. TV's are now essentially a computer, so why don't they treat it like one?

Title: Origin #PC won't stop beeping! Can this computer be fixed? #tech #technology #shorts
Description: This big old Origin laptop came into my computer repair shop because it won't stop beeping after the customer replaced the thermal paste. This old laptop is a real chonker, and the tech packed into here was top of the line back in the day. But even after new thermal paste and fans, this pc still keeps beeping, indicating damage on the motherboard. But the amount of labor to track down the issue without schematics, will cost more than this old technology is even worth. Which is always the problem with motherboard issues in high-cost countries like the US, leading to more e-waste.

Title: The Rise And Fall of the "Tech Bro"
Description:

All materials in these videos are for educational purposes only and fall within the guidelines of fair use. No copyright infringement intended. This video does not provide investment or financial advice of any kind.

#tech #business #career 

-----

Before the year 2000, if you wanted to make a lot of money in a predictable career you needed a nice suit and an important looking business card. Your options where finance, medicine, law or senior company management if you were lucky. 


But then… just a few years later at around about the same time as those people in their fancy suits were blowing up the global economy a new breed of millionaire was entering the mainstream. 

They replaced the puffer vests and Bloomberg terminals with flip flops and vim terminals… 

Tech bro’s worked fewer hours, had better perks and in many cases made better money than their peers in more traditional high-income roles…

What’s more is that people didn’t hate them… 

Executives, bankers and their fancy lawyers were rightfully blamed for enriching themselves by leeching off a broken system that cost people their homes, their jobs, and their futures… 

Meanwhile people loved the idea of hacky sack playing nerds making millions by actually making stuff that improved our lives… 

But now… 15 years later the tech bros became everything they promised to destroy… and they kind of destroyed themselves in the process…

For a while you could have a great degree of confidence in becoming filthy rich by putting in a few years at a major Silicon Valley tech company… but this all relied on a stream of money that wasn’t coming from nowhere… 

Venture capital, the firms that ACTUALLY invest in early-stage start-ups to develop their new technology NEVER again actually reached the level of financing it did during the dot com bubble. 

That was… until something changed in 2021… 

So it’s time to learn How Money Works to find out how Tech Bro’s ruined tech for themselves…

Title: Where Are Laid Off Tech Employees Going? | CNBC Marathon
Description:
CNBC explores challenges currently facing U.S. tech workers, including mass layoffs, widespread cuts in company budgets, and threats of deportation for H-1B visa holders.

"The layoffs to the start of 2024 signal a dramatic shift in the tech industry," said Jeff Shulman, professor at the University of Washington's Foster School of Business. The number of tech sector layoffs in 2024 has been outpacing the number of terminations in 2023. So far, about 42,324 tech employees were let go in 2024, according to

Layoffs.fyi, which tracks layoffs in the tech industry.

While layoffs have put stress on the workforce, a booming artificial intelligence market is giving the industry a renewed sense of optimism. Generative AI startup deals announced or finalized in the first quarter of this year totaled more than $12 billion compared to about $4.5 billion invested in the space last year, according to PitchBook.

On July 16, 2023, Canada opened visa applications for a pilot program that would allow up to 10,000 H-1B visa holders in the United States to apply for a three-year open-work permit in Canada. H-1B holders are highly educated and specialized foreign workers that work in fields such as tech. After massive layoffs in the tech industry, this was a lifeline for H-1B holders who needed to find a new job or face deportation.

About the video: “There's a very simple answer for why we need this. In one word, it's connection. Touch is what connects us to each other and it connects us to the world around us. And if I can actually reach and feel something, it's real to me.”

Subscribe to Freethink on YouTube ► https://freeth.ink/youtube-subscribe

VR experiences are getting increasingly visually impressive. Some of the graphics in virtual worlds are so advanced that they seem almost indistinguishable from our world of reality. But there’s still one key element that's missing to create a fully immersive experience  – a sense of touch. 

What if we could hack our nervous systems so that virtual worlds also included a realistic sense of touch? Afference has found a way to create an interface between the digital realm and your nervous system with tech that talks directly to your nerves using small electrical signals, and we got an exclusive test of the company’s harness, The Phantom. 

Currently, this groundbreaking tech can allow users to experience basic sensations, but over time it'll be able to do far more, lending visual mediums a whole new dimension to speak through.

Title: What do tech pioneers think about the AI revolution? - BBC World Service
Description:
Three leading engineers discuss the impact of the AI revolution.

Click here to subscribe to our channel 👉🏽 https://bbc.in/3VyyriM

Intelligent machines are remaking our world. The speed of their improvement is accelerating fast and every day there are more things they can do better than us. There are risks, but the opportunities for human society are enormous. 

Three engineers at the forefront of that revolution come to London to join Caroline Steel and a public audience at the Great Hall of Imperial College.

Regina Barzilay from MIT created a major breakthrough in detecting early stage breast cancer. She also led the team that used machine learning to discover Halicin, the first new antibiotic in 30 years. 

David Silver is Principal Research Scientist at Google DeepMind. He led the AlphaGo team that built the AI to defeat the world’s best human player of Go. 

Paolo Pirjanian founded Embodied, and is a pioneer in developing emotionally intelligent robots to aid child development.

Title: Where Are Laid Off Tech Employees Going? | CNBC Marathon
Description:
CNBC explores challenges currently facing U.S. tech workers, including mass layoffs, widespread cuts in company budgets, and threats of deportation for H-1B visa holders.

"The layoffs to the start of 2024 signal a dramatic shift in the tech industry," said Jeff Shulman, professor at the University of Washington's Foster School of Business. The number of tech sector layoffs in 2024 has been outpacing the number of terminations in 2023. So far, about 42,324 tech employees were let go in 2024, according to

Layoffs.fyi, which tracks layoffs in the tech industry.

While layoffs have put stress on the workforce, a booming artificial intelligence market is giving the industry a renewed sense of optimism. Generative AI startup deals announced or finalized in the first quarter of this year totaled more than $12 billion compared to about $4.5 billion invested in the space last year, according to PitchBook.

On July 16, 2023, Canada opened visa applications for a pilot program that would allow up to 10,000 H-1B visa holders in the United States to apply for a three-year open-work permit in Canada. H-1B holders are highly educated and specialized foreign workers that work in fields such as tech. After massive layoffs in the tech industry, this was a lifeline for H-1B holders who needed to find a new job or face deportation.

Chapters:
00:00 Introduction
00:47 Why Widespread Tech Layoffs Keep Happening Despite A Strong U.S. Economy (Published February 2024)

Title: Tita Lau LIVE @ Get Closer, Miami, USA, Tech House / House
Description:
Tita Lau recorded live in Miami at  @JamesHype  's 'GET CLOSER' event.
 
We had so many things against us for this shoot T-Gang 🫠 The worst rain storm I've ever experienced in Miami, the police showing up during my set so had to cut it earlier than planned (check my face when I get told 🥲) and shortly after I hit play, a random lady ran straight up to me, started screaming in my face and then twerked on me 🤣 (I turned the scream down for fear of your ears and speakers lol) I'll share the full audio on Instagram... It was harmless but also I had no idea what she was going to do to me and I couldn't stop because we were on a strict time slot. The show must go on! That being said, the energy from T-Gang and Hypefam was on another level and even the police ended up staying for the set 😝

Title: Best Phones 2024 (I've Tested Over 60!) | Mid-Range, Camera, Gaming & More
Description:
The best smartphones of 2024 reviewed, after testing over five dozen - including my favourite camera phone, budget-friendly flagship Android handsets, mid-range mobiles, compact devices and more. What's your own selection of the top phones as we hit 2025?

Choosing the greatest tech from the past twelve months is always tough, even when narrowed down to the smartphones I've personally used. Rather than offering up what I think is the 'best', I've gone for what I'd personally choose in each category.

I've fully tested all of these phones in 2024, from the most capable camera handsets to the most powerful gaming pocket-fillers. With Snapdragon 8 Elite smartphones already emerging, that last category in particular was quite easy to fill. I've also reviewed a few foldables, and quite a lot of mid-range devices. In fact, choosing my favourite mid-ranger was probably the hardest of all.

Let us know your own favourite 'best phone' of 2024 in the comments and stay tuned for even more unboxing and review videos as we hit the new year - the launches aren't over yet!

Title: Vivo X200 Pro, Best Flagship Phone for 2025? | Two Weeks Later...
Description:
Reviewing the Vivo X200 Pro (global edition) after nearly two weeks of using as my full time phone. From its Zeiss camera tech to the gaming smarts and battery life, the Vivo X200 Pro has a lot of highlights. Personally I prefer the software experience on the Find X8 Pro etc, but vs the iPhone 16 Pro Max, this is a clear winner.

First up, the triple camera setup offers impressive flexibility for everyday photography and video capture. The Vivo X200 Pro's telephoto lens in particular worked well, for everything from portraits to night shots, while the ultra-wide offers macro support.

Gamers will also love the Dimensity 9400 which runs the show. Mediatek's chipset can handle games like Wuthering Waves and Genshin Impact on the highest graphics settings, while the Vivo X200 Pro remains reassuringly cool. Or at least, doesn't heat up as much as the X100 series.

Battery life is also among the very best of 2024 phones. As long as you aren't gaming for hours, you should make it through a full day on a single charge of the 6000mAh battery. And the Vivo X200 Pro also boasts a gorgeous screen and stereo speakers.
